# Phase 2 gate: this source compiles via stage1.wasm with NOTHING
# prepended — no strata bundle, no stdlib, no WASI declarations.
#
# The program is intentionally tiny: a single integer constant
# evaluated at top level, which the Phase 1 _start synthesis wraps
# into the WASI entry.  No platform externs, no io.si calls.
#
# What this proves: stage1.wasm's embedded strata source (from
# src/strata/*.si, baked in at build time as EMBEDDED_BUNDLE) is
# correctly copied to the head of the source buffer at runtime and
# parsed before stdin, so the operators / definition keywords used
# below resolve via the registry without the caller bundling
# anything.

@fn add a:Int, b:Int := { a + b };

&add 20, 22;
